ons:\n*   **Weighted Average Monthly Revenue:** Assumed at **$12** for global market sizing.\n*   **SuperGrok Pricing Tiers:** \n    *   **$30 / month** in high-income countries.\n    *   **$8 / month** in upper-middle and lower-middle-income countries.\n    *   Significantly lower in low-income countries.\n*   **Total Addressable Market (TAM):** The consumer AI subscription market opportunity is estimated at an annualized **~$760 billion** (based on ~5.5 billion global individuals aged 10+ multiplied by the $12 weighted average).\n\n### 4. Segment Economics & Financial Metrics (AI Segment)\nThe AI segment is currently operating at a significant loss due to massive capital expenditures and R&D scaling for Grok and data center infrastructure.\n\n**Profitability & Margins:**\n*   **Segment Loss from Operations:**\n    *   *Q1 2026:* **$(2,469) million** (vs. $(936)M in Q1 2025)\n    *   *FY 2025:* **$(6,355) million** (vs. $(1,561)M in FY 2024)\n*   **Segment Adjusted EBITDA:**\n    *   *Q1 2026:* **$(609) million** (vs. $(112)M in Q1 2025)\n    *   *FY 2025:* **$(1,237) million** (vs. $347M in FY 2024)\n\n**Cost of Revenue (AI Segment):**\n*   *Q1 2026:* Increased by **$5 million** (+1.1% YoY). Driven by a **$71 million** increase in revenue share/content creator expenses and **$18 million** in higher payment processing fees.\n*   *FY 2025:* Increased by **$491 million** (+29.1% YoY). Primarily driven by **$412 million** in higher infrastructure and cloud computing costs attributable to increased subscriber revenue, plus **$90 million** in higher employee compensation.\n\n**Research & Development (AI Segment):**\n*   *Q1 2026:* Increased by **$1,471 million** (+125.7% YoY).\n*   *FY 2025:* Increased by **$3,888 million** (+149.5% YoY).\n*   *Primary Drivers:* Massive depreciation of GPU hardware, cloud computing costs, and data center infrastructure expansions required to train Grok and next-generation AI models.\n\n### 5. Infrastructure & Compute Unit Economics\n*  